@startuml implementation-lifecycle
title Implementation Plugin — Lifecycle (per livespec-impl-*)
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam BackgroundColor #fafafa
skinparam ArrowColor #000000
skinparam ArrowFontColor #000000
skinparam ArrowFontSize 11
skinparam ArrowThickness 1.3
skinparam nodesep 16
skinparam ranksep 26
hide stereotype

skinparam rectangle {
  BackgroundColor #d6e6f5
  BorderColor #1f4768
  FontColor #111
  RoundCorner 8
}
skinparam database {
  BackgroundColor #f5ead5
  BorderColor #5a4319
  FontColor #111
}
skinparam component {
  BackgroundColor #e0d4ec
  BorderColor #5a3a72
  FontColor #111
}
skinparam package {
  FontColor #111
  FontSize 13
  FontStyle bold
  BorderColor #444
  BorderThickness 2
}

package "SPEC SIDE (read-only here)" as SpecPkg #fde8ec {
  database "SPECIFICATION/" as Spec #f5d76e
  database "history/vNNN/" as History
  rectangle "/livespec:propose-changes" as Propose
}

package "IMPLEMENTATION SIDE" as ImplPkg #e3f0e3 {
  rectangle "/livespec-impl-*:\ncapture-impl-gaps" as CaptureImplGaps
  rectangle "/livespec-impl-*:\ncapture-spec-drift" as CaptureSpecDrift
  rectangle "/livespec-impl-*:\ncapture-work-item" as CaptureWorkItem
  rectangle "/livespec-impl-*:\nimplement" as Implement

  component "Spec Reader\n(impl-plugin adapter)" as SpecReader

  database "Implementation\n(code, tests, config,\ninfra, plugins)" as Impl #f5d76e
  database "Work Items\n(plugin-specific:\nbd / JSONL / GitLab / ...)" as WorkItems
}

' Cross-boundary: spec content flows to the impl-side Spec Reader
Spec -[#a02020,thickness=2]-> SpecReader
History -[#a02020,thickness=2]-> SpecReader

' Spec Reader fans out to impl-side consumers
SpecReader --> CaptureImplGaps
SpecReader --> CaptureSpecDrift
SpecReader --> Implement

' Capture Impl Gaps: mechanical spec→impl gap detection
Impl --> CaptureImplGaps
CaptureImplGaps --> WorkItems : files gap-tied items\n(gap-id label,\nper-gap user consent)

' Capture Spec Drift: heuristic impl→spec drift detection
Impl --> CaptureSpecDrift

' Cross-boundary: drift findings feed back to Propose Change
CaptureSpecDrift -[#a02020,thickness=2]-> Propose : drift findings\n(per-finding user consent)

' Capture Work Item: direct freeform filing (bugs, refactors, tactical tasks)
CaptureWorkItem --> WorkItems : files freeform item\n(no gap-id)

' Implement drains work items into the realized implementation
WorkItems --> Implement : leaf-level pick
Implement --> Impl : Red → Green code cycle
Implement --> WorkItems : close — branched by\norigin × disposition

note right of CaptureImplGaps : Mechanical: enumerate spec rules,\ncheck impl for each. Detection is\nin-memory and ephemeral — no persistent\nintermediate artifact. Items it files carry\na gap-id:gap-NNNN label tying back to the\noriginating spec rule, which makes closure\nverifiable.

note right of CaptureSpecDrift : LLM-driven heuristic: every line of impl\nis "doing something"; signal-to-noise is\nbrutal. Asymmetric counterpart to\ncapture-impl-gaps — separate skill because\nmerging would hide the mechanical-vs-heuristic\nreliability gap.

note bottom of Implement : Closure branches on origin × disposition:\n• gap-tied fix → verify via re-run of\n  capture-impl-gaps in dry-run; record\n  audit fields (resolution method,\n  verification timestamp, commits, files).\n• freeform fix → close with --reason; no\n  verification step.\n• non-fix (wontfix/duplicate/spec-revised/\n  no-longer-applicable/resolved-out-of-band)\n  → close with reason; no verification, no\n  audit fields.

note left of SpecReader : Impl-side adapter. Required capabilities:\n• read current Specification\n• read Specification History\n• report current spec version (vNNN)\n• read/summarize diffs between versions\nInternals are plugin-specific: thin\npass-through, cached, indexed, embedded,\nor RAG-style retrieval.

@enduml
